&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Labviva, our marketplace is only as strong as our supplier ecosystem. We are seeking a dynamic, results-driven&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Manager, Supplier Growth &amp;amp; Partnerships&lt;/strong&gt; who deeply understands the supplier mindset, operational workflows, and commercial drivers. This isn&#39;t a traditional SaaS sales role; you will be a dedicated business develpment manager of Labviva’s supplier network, specifically targeting Life Sciences, R&amp;amp;D, and MRO (office and electronics) materials. &lt;strong&gt;Your primary mission is to expand and optimize our supplier portfolio&lt;/strong&gt;. You will leverage your firsthand experience working with or within supplier organizations to identify, secure, and nurture strategic relationships, ensuring suppliers see Labviva not just as a platform, but as their premier growth channel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Contribute&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex business development and onboarding cycles to bring high-value Life Sciences and MRO suppliers into the Labviva ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Articulate the strategic and financial value of Labviva to potential partners, helping them navigate digital catalog integration, marketplace logistics, and e-procurement alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain deep, trusted relationships with key supplier stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor supplier engagement and performance metrics, analyzing data trends to help partners maximize their sales volume and operational efficiency on the Labviva platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product, marketing, and implementation teams to ensure our platform&#39;s capabilities continuously evolve to solve real-world supplier pain points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead quarterly business reviews with core suppliers, aligning their commercial goals with Labviva’s growth trajectory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the face of Labviva’s supplier network at major industry events, conferences, and trade shows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring to the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7+ years&lt;/strong&gt; of experience in business development, account management, or commercial operation &lt;strong&gt;specifically working within a supplier organization, a distributor, or directly managing B2B supplier networks.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with the Life Sciences, R&amp;amp;D, or industrial MRO supply chains. You know how manufacturers and distributors operate, how they price, and how they manage inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong understanding of B2B procurement processes, e-commerce marketplaces, and digital purchasing workflows (e.g., PunchOut catalogs, ERP integrations).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of navigating complex corporate structures, overcoming commercial friction, and closing mutually beneficial partnership agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in business, life sciences, supply chain management, or a related field; an MBA is a distinct advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with CRM platforms (e.g., HubSpot) and data analysis tools to track partner health and pipeline metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
