&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Labviva’s marketplace is a two-sided e-commerce platform which allows enterprise clients to connect their scientists and laboratory administrators to millions of scientific products offered by a variety of different vendors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a&lt;strong&gt; Senior Fullstack Engineer for the e-commerce PlatformTeam&lt;/strong&gt;, you will help advance our core purchasing platform to provide a modern e-commerce experience specifically tailored for scientific users.&amp;nbsp; This includes allowing scientists to search millions of data rich records when ordering equipment, chemicals, and lab consumables while providing suppliers with rich analytics about marketplace behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a fit for the role if you enjoy creating comprehensive end-to-end solutions within a collaborative environment. Experience with e-commerce platforms or enterprise web applications is a plus. You are thoughtful in your approach to design and engineer solutions that meet business demands while optimizing for system health, security, and long-term maintenance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Boston Headquarters at 239 Causeway Street, Suite 500, Boston, MA. This is a hybrid role 3 days a week in the office (Tues,Wed,Thurs).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note: Only considering applicants that reside in the greater Boston, Massachusetts area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Contribute&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
